1
00:00:12,340 --> 00:00:13,729
[Team Leader Baek Su Jeong]

2
00:00:13,730 --> 00:00:16,420
[Moon Ga Young]

3
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:19,129
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

4
00:00:19,130 --> 00:00:21,989
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

5
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:23,830
[Yongsung's successor. [The new chaebol director?]

6
00:00:25,850 --> 00:00:27,980
[Im Se Mi]

7
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,770
[Kwak Shi Yang]

8
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:45,019
[My Dearest Enemy]

9
00:00:45,020 --> 00:00:47,939
[This series is fictional.]

10
00:00:47,940 --> 00:00:49,920
[Characters and settings are fictional.]

11
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:03,170
Why are you crying?

12
00:01:04,470 --> 00:01:06,570
When I look at you like this...

13
00:01:10,310 --> 00:01:12,670
You look even more angelic.

14
00:01:14,570 --> 00:01:17,180
Oh my, really.

15
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:25,920
Now that I think about it, you said the same thing when we first met.

16
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:31,840
What is Melek?

17
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:34,639
Always...

18
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:37,569
You would say such things without any shame.

19
00:01:37,570 --> 00:01:40,370
But you really do look like an angel.

20
00:01:41,170 --> 00:01:43,910
You were like that then, and you are like that now.

21
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:49,130
I'll make you some soup. Sleep a little longer.

22
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,049
[Chapter 10]

23
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:05,569
Take the medicine again before bed. Don't forget.

24
00:02:05,570 --> 00:02:07,700
I'm feeling better now.

25
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,539
No, you're not.

26
00:02:09,540 --> 00:02:11,240
I'm really fine.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,140
Buy it anyway. You never know.

28
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,569
Are you really going?

29
00:02:21,570 --> 00:02:23,559
Why don't you stay a little longer?

30
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,189
I have to go. It's getting late.

31
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,169
You should rest today.

32
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:31,250
We can be together from now on.

33
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:36,280
Okay. You should rest at home too.

34
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,670
Thank you.

35
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,090
See you tomorrow.

36
00:03:01,810 --> 00:03:03,519
Get home safely.

37
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:05,790
Call me when you arrive.

38
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,710
I can't do it.

39
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:37,730
I can't leave you.

40
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,730
Please stay with me.

41
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,359
What's wrong?

42
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,050
When did I fall asleep?

43
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:33,729
Baek Su Jeong.

44
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:35,819
Dad, you're up.

45
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:42,170
Well, I need to get back to work—were you with the director?

46
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,450
Have you reconciled?

47
00:05:48,570 --> 00:05:50,199
Yes.

48
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,979
Su Jeong's family isn't a normal family.

49
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:55,059
According to the articles, many eyes are on him.

50
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,839
A lot of people are talking.

51
00:05:56,840 --> 00:06:00,790
You know I don't care about things like that.

52
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:06,389
I really love him/her.

53
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:09,710
So, can't you just give permission?

54
00:06:15,090 --> 00:06:17,450
What does "to allow" mean?

55
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:22,840
I need to trust your decision.

56
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:27,839
But, Su Jeong, tell me you're having a hard time.

57
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,699
Just keep it inside.

58
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,750
I don't care about anything else.

59
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:34,669
I just want you to be happy.

60
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:36,560
That's enough.

61
00:06:38,340 --> 00:06:39,919
Okay.

62
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,499
Anyway. Now go to work.

63
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,799
Okay, I'll go.

64
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:46,350
But staying outside...

65
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:50,029
Just don't get caught.

66
00:06:50,030 --> 00:06:52,750
Okay, I'll never get caught.

67
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:56,970
Tell him you won't stay out all night!

68
00:07:06,010 --> 00:07:07,540
[Chief Secretary]

69
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,429
Director Ban.

70
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:17,529
Yes.

71
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:21,300
You are dismissed from your job effective today.

72
00:07:38,610 --> 00:07:41,640
I knew this would happen.

73
00:07:43,210 --> 00:07:48,439
Didn't you say nothing was wrong?

74
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,310
Yes, Madam President.

75
00:07:51,210 --> 00:07:53,189
It is clearly evident that...

76
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:56,569
There's nothing between them.

77
00:07:56,570 --> 00:08:00,780
I'm sorry I disappointed you.

78
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,650
[Resignation Letter]

79
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:08,330
Thank you for everything.

80
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:12,909
[Notice of Termination]

81
00:08:12,910 --> 00:08:14,179
[Strategy Team Director Ban Ju Yeon]

82
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:15,580
[Bbanjju]

83
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:21,290
The customer is currently unavailable.

84
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:25,860
The mayor is going too far.

85
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:28,679
Was the director fired?

86
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,049
Suddenly?

87
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:32,399
Is this about the rumor concerning the Team Leader?

88
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,739
I can't be.

89
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:35,699
There's no other way to explain it.

90
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:38,069
And overnight? In the middle of the project?

91
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:40,970
But still. Layoffs?

92
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:45,700
- What will our project be? - Team Leader.

93
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:53,120
Director...

94
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:58,420
Team Leader!

95
00:09:01,930 --> 00:09:03,189
The call is not going through.

96
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:05,670
You will be connected...

97
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:12,029
What happened to the manager, the director, all of a sudden?

98
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,579
You're in too much of a hurry.

99
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:17,429
You're no longer hiding your relationship.

100
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:18,679
No problem.

101
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:21,919
The mayor knows now, too.

102
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,056
Sir?

103
00:09:23,068 --> 00:09:26,509
He knows when the director comes in and out of his house.

104
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,809
He knows everything.

105
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:31,029
Apparently, he had many guards.

106
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:33,020
This is what happened...

107
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,400
Kwon is the manager.

108
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,970
I am resigning.

109
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:45,039
- Why? - Because I knew it from the beginning.

110
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:48,140
But I kept it a secret.

111
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:59,249
Take good care of the director.

112
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:04,400
But I'm glad someone like you is by his side.

113
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:21,660
[Kwon In Gyeong, Manager]

114
00:10:25,780 --> 00:10:29,630
Director, where is the president right now?

115
00:10:52,930 --> 00:10:54,690
Madam President.

116
00:10:58,090 --> 00:10:59,949
How do you get in here?

117
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,679
I know you're unhappy...

118
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,179
about our relationship.

119
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:08,280
But I won't let my personal feelings put Yongsung in danger,

120
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:12,070
That's why—I told you it would end if you disappointed me.

121
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:20,420
Grandmother.

122
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:32,970
You know, I...

123
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:37,499
I did everything for Yongsung.

124
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,199
I will be better from now on.

125
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,459
As your granddaughter, I will work even harder.

126
00:11:42,460 --> 00:11:48,050
I thought I could replace you, but you turned out to be flawed.

127
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:53,179
The fact that you're related to me disgusts me.

128
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:55,560
What about me?

129
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:57,651
What?

130
00:11:57,663 --> 00:12:01,749
Since my parents passed away, I haven't been able to freely grieve or rejoice.

131
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:03,849
Because I was always an unworthy grandchild.

132
00:12:03,850 --> 00:12:08,799
No matter how painful it was, I persevered and worked very hard every day.

133
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:13,559
I thought that if I lived the way you wanted, one day you would accept me.

134
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:17,419
I'm trying to meet your standards.

135
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:20,220
But I can't even do it...

136
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:24,669
- To love him? - Of course not.

137
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:26,859
You said you wanted to be my heir.

138
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:28,449
Love?

139
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:33,090
With a subordinate, the daughter of a hardware store owner?

140
00:12:33,930 --> 00:12:40,010
I should never have hired an unqualified person.

141
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:44,630
I think...

142
00:12:47,230 --> 00:12:50,629
I could never be good enough for you.

143
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:52,360
TRUE.

144
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,630
[Yongsung]

145
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,609
Ben...

146
00:13:41,610 --> 00:13:43,649
I will fill my father's place.

147
00:13:43,650 --> 00:13:48,899
I thought I could replace you, but you turned out to be flawed.

148
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:53,200
The fact that you're related to me disgusts me.

149
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:32,669
Are you ok?

150
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:35,280
Call me when you see this.

151
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:43,869
I am good.

152
00:14:43,870 --> 00:14:46,370
I'm sorry for worrying you.

153
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:51,310
See you after work.

154
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,919
Where are you?

155
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,370
I'm leaving now.

156
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:09,809
Here you are.

157
00:15:09,810 --> 00:15:11,459
You must be hungry.

158
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:12,799
What should we eat?

159
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:16,779
Director, you can tell the president that we're leaving.

160
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,109
I really don't care.

161
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:19,959
There's no need to deny our relationship.

162
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,240
And we shouldn't.

163
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:25,380
I apologize for everything.

164
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:31,799
Where should we go?

165
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,740
Now I can go on dates anywhere.

166
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:37,009
You are right.

167
00:15:37,010 --> 00:15:39,230
Now we can do it.

168
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,520
We can also hold hands like this.

169
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:46,780
I like it.

170
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:52,969
You can freely go to concerts as well.

171
00:15:52,970 --> 00:15:57,069
Since I went public, I never thought I'd be able to go to a concert again.

172
00:15:57,070 --> 00:16:00,350
Now I can move on to the next one.

173
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:03,929
Shall we go together?

174
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:06,159
Of course, I'd love to go with you.

175
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:09,256
From now on, the things you do alone...

176
00:16:09,268 --> 00:16:12,029
...I'll do it together. No matter what.

177
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:14,059
Sounds good.

178
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:17,129
I'll be quite well.

179
00:16:17,130 --> 00:16:19,629
Then you will continue to be fine.

180
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:22,900
Because I'll stay with you.

181
00:16:29,810 --> 00:16:32,420
How can I not worry?

182
00:16:33,310 --> 00:16:35,780
I'm with Su Jeong.

183
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:40,069
Kim Shin Won.

184
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:42,689
Why is it so hard to see you these days?

185
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:44,719
Because I'm with my girlfriend.

186
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,369
Do you think I don't know this?

187
00:16:46,370 --> 00:16:48,839
Because you've been coming home less often lately.

188
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,989
My son.

189
00:16:50,990 --> 00:16:53,129
You said you didn't paint portraits.

190
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:54,929
But what are you working on now?

191
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,259
I wanted to draw it just once.

192
00:16:57,260 --> 00:16:59,169
It would later make a lovely gift.

193
00:16:59,170 --> 00:17:03,470
It seems like you've finally found the right person.

194
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:06,770
I think so too.

195
00:17:07,490 --> 00:17:09,569
Are you even considering marrying him?

196
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:11,939
I haven't thought about that yet, but...

197
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:13,839
How should I say this?

198
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:15,649
I always want to be with him.

199
00:17:15,650 --> 00:17:17,889
I don't want to be separated from him.

200
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:24,260
If I could share a lifetime with him/her like I did with the two of you, I would definitely be happy.

201
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:32,840
I never expected to see you dressed like this.

202
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:36,140
I'm not your boss anymore.

203
00:17:36,940 --> 00:17:39,100
Why did you do this?

204
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:43,329
The truth is you upset the President's wife.

205
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:45,229
I don't understand this.

206
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,399
Do you know...

207
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:52,700
When did I start to respect and admire the president?

208
00:17:53,660 --> 00:18:00,359
This may seem cruel to you, but it was after she lost her son.

209
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:10,600
Seeing how strong he was at that time, I thought, 'I can trust someone like that.'

210
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:16,730
You don't like espresso, do you?

211
00:18:17,390 --> 00:18:21,199
Sometimes you go to concerts.

212
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:26,589
I didn't check the contents of the packages you ordered under that strange name.

213
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:29,030
When you know all of this,

214
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,639
Why didn't you tell him?

215
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:35,769
You hid these things so you could be the person he wanted you to be.

216
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:42,939
Hiding and suppressing your emotions hasn't been easy, but you've persevered.

217
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:47,809
This side of her looked very much like the president.

218
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:52,699
And I thought he was the heir she had in mind.

219
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,669
- Then, this time too- - No.

220
00:18:55,670 --> 00:19:00,880
I was just an ordinary person drawn to love.

221
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:07,419
Being an heir is nice, but I've known you since you were a child.

222
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:13,460
I thought it would be nice for you to be happy with someone you love.

223
00:19:19,330 --> 00:19:22,089
So, Manager Kwon...

224
00:19:22,090 --> 00:19:23,990
That's how you felt.

225
00:19:24,660 --> 00:19:27,770
Yes. I felt it.

226
00:19:36,330 --> 00:19:40,930
Thank you for working with me during this time.

227
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,210
What should I do now?

228
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:12,470
What are you going to do now?

229
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:16,539
Would you like to read comic books in the attic?

230
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:19,119
I think Su Bin is home.

231
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,940
Okay.

232
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,289
I'm approaching the shop now.

233
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:40,029
What? I'm still coming back from grocery shopping.

234
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,769
No problem. I can wait.

235
00:20:41,770 --> 00:20:43,349
I took half a day off today.

236
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:45,149
We really need to watch a movie today.

237
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:48,259
We can't just suddenly go to a hotel like last time.

238
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:51,509
Did you gladly change your destination?

239
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:55,769
Oh dear. We're on the same page too often.

240
00:20:55,770 --> 00:20:58,060
Okay, see you later.

241
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:25,949
What?

242
00:21:25,950 --> 00:21:29,200
What are you doing here at this hour?

243
00:21:34,010 --> 00:21:38,139
So, your grandmother kicked you out and you lost your job.

244
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:40,689
This is for you...

245
00:21:40,690 --> 00:21:44,080
It means you're unemployed. Just like me.

246
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:46,429
Unemployed?

247
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,849
Aren't you?

248
00:21:48,850 --> 00:21:51,500
Is there anything you can do?

249
00:21:52,370 --> 00:21:54,669
No.

250
00:21:54,670 --> 00:21:57,949
That's why you wanted to wait for Sister at our place.

251
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:04,799
Not exactly—by the way, what exactly do you like about him?

252
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,129
She's beautiful.

253
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:08,339
Are you out of your mind?

254
00:22:08,340 --> 00:22:10,169
Going mad with love is not a sin.

255
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:12,820
Aman, hard.

256
00:22:13,770 --> 00:22:17,239
I think I'm going to throw up. Please stop talking.

257
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:21,050
And he loves me just the way I am.

258
00:22:21,890 --> 00:22:24,429
She cried because of the breakup.

259
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:27,849
But you're both completely madly in love. Really.

260
00:22:27,850 --> 00:22:30,649
Did Su Jeong cry?

261
00:22:30,650 --> 00:22:31,979
Yes.

262
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:34,469
My father and I have never seen her cry like this before.

263
00:22:34,470 --> 00:22:37,399
That sent shivers down my spine... just kidding.

264
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,419
Thinking about it, he had done the same thing back then.

265
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:42,269
Because of the Black Dragon, or whatever it is.

266
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:43,379
Black Dragon.

267
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:45,729
There is such a man. He was her first love.

268
00:22:45,730 --> 00:22:50,309
Dark days. If he finds out I know, he'll bite his tongue and kill himself.

269
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:53,459
Did she cry a lot then too?

270
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,749
Yes.

271
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:56,799
He didn't eat for days.

272
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:59,819
My father was very worried too, but he couldn't show it.

273
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:02,600
It was the worst thing he ever did.

274
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,719
Ye.

275
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:07,450
Okay.

276
00:23:13,490 --> 00:23:16,009
[No. 1 Hardware]

277
00:23:16,010 --> 00:23:17,699
Baba.

278
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,800
Give me the heavy things.

279
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,029
What brought you here?

280
00:23:22,030 --> 00:23:25,139
I don't know. Suddenly he wants to help you.

281
00:23:25,140 --> 00:23:26,589
He must be busy.

282
00:23:26,590 --> 00:23:28,839
No. Unemployed.

283
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:30,389
I will do everything I can to help you.

284
00:23:30,390 --> 00:23:34,079
I have no skills, but I have power.

285
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:36,869
I don't think so.

286
00:23:36,870 --> 00:23:38,949
Do you see?

287
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:41,419
Then follow me.

288
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:43,029
- Me too? - Yes, help him.

289
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:44,189
B-What?

290
00:23:44,190 --> 00:23:47,390
I was planning to relax on my day off.

291
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:51,150
- Give it to me. - Okay.

292
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,950
Where should I start?

293
00:23:55,590 --> 00:23:57,749
You said you have no skills.

294
00:23:57,750 --> 00:23:59,649
Can you do these things?

295
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:01,889
You just need to replace the door handle.

296
00:24:01,890 --> 00:24:06,059
Of course. I'll try to handle it myself.

297
00:24:06,060 --> 00:24:08,079
If you can't do it, let me know.

298
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:10,789
Su Jeong does this with her eyes closed.

299
00:24:10,790 --> 00:24:13,910
I'm bad at being bad at something.

300
00:24:19,370 --> 00:24:21,799
Is he going to do it with his bare hands?

301
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,340
Go help him.

302
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:35,609
How can I do this...?

303
00:24:35,610 --> 00:24:39,189
If you do that, you'll have to glue it.

304
00:24:39,190 --> 00:24:42,319
This is how you do it. Do you understand?

305
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:44,419
And you... No.

306
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:47,059
Use this to solve it.

307
00:24:47,060 --> 00:24:50,279
I'll try it myself then.

308
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,809
Be careful. Then...

309
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:54,379
Keep this for me.

310
00:24:54,380 --> 00:24:56,379
- I'll hold it. - Okay.

311
00:24:56,380 --> 00:24:58,189
Is it expensive?

312
00:24:58,190 --> 00:25:01,359
Well, I really don't know.

313
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:02,770
Well...

314
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:05,599
No, no, no.

315
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:09,279
If you don't know how to do that, you'd better let me know.

316
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:11,490
Thank you for teaching me.

317
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:14,679
- I can do it well. - Can you?

318
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,890
Okay.

319
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:27,110
Dad, I've accomplished this important task.

320
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,209
You're doing the same thing, aren't you?

321
00:25:30,210 --> 00:25:33,180
- Opposite direction. - Same direction, right?

322
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:47,320
Why isn't he/she answering?

323
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:52,709
Guess what your boyfriend is doing.

324
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:54,340
What?

325
00:25:57,880 --> 00:26:01,939
There is a great deal of concern about the vacant director position.

326
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:06,490
Also, regarding the heir other than Director Ban-

327
00:26:07,830 --> 00:26:11,780
Do you think there's no one who can change him?

328
00:26:13,050 --> 00:26:17,339
Yongsung Trading'den Park Ji Cheol'u ara.

329
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:18,739
Yes.

330
00:26:18,740 --> 00:26:23,709
For Team Leader Baek Su Jeong - Get rid of him quietly.

331
00:26:23,710 --> 00:26:25,220
Okay.

332
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,349
You worked very hard today.

333
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:40,529
Why don't we have dinner together?

334
00:26:40,530 --> 00:26:43,249
Yes, I will enjoy it.

335
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:46,229
How do you know you'll enjoy it?

336
00:26:46,230 --> 00:26:49,949
What are we going to eat today?

337
00:26:49,950 --> 00:26:51,239
Shall I cook it then?

338
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:56,350
I'm strong, but I can also cook.

339
00:26:57,050 --> 00:26:59,290
I don't think you can do it.

340
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:19,239
He spent the whole day trying to impress you.

341
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:21,519
That was pretty good, wasn't it?

342
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:24,999
- Trying to impress me? - You're your girlfriend's father.

343
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,919
That's right. You don't have to do that.

344
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:30,119
As long as Su Jeong is happy, I am happy.

345
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:31,359
Hey, come on.

346
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:33,129
I know you don't trust him.

347
00:27:33,130 --> 00:27:34,329
Did I not trust you?

348
00:27:34,330 --> 00:27:37,189
Did I not trust you? That's not true.

349
00:27:37,190 --> 00:27:39,449
Of course, you're worried.

350
00:27:39,450 --> 00:27:42,739
I don't come from a normal background.

351
00:27:42,740 --> 00:27:46,799
You trust Su Jeong, but not me.

352
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:51,579
That's my situation right now, but I'll make sure you don't worry.

353
00:27:51,580 --> 00:27:57,190
No matter what, I won't make her cry or leave her alone.

354
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:02,599
I'm such a bad father.

355
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:06,200
All I could do was trust him, and nothing else.

356
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:09,339
But thanks to you, I feel relieved.

357
00:28:09,340 --> 00:28:12,610
I'll make sure you don't have to worry.

358
00:28:20,790 --> 00:28:23,169
Su Jeong, welcome.

359
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:24,649
What are you doing?

360
00:28:24,650 --> 00:28:26,199
What's this headscarf all about?

361
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:27,789
Welcome, Su Jeong. Let's eat.

362
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:31,279
My son-in-law is a fantastic cook.

363
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:35,949
- What? - I learned to cook when I was a child.

364
00:28:35,950 --> 00:28:38,769
Galbijjim is amazing, Brother-in-law.

365
00:28:38,770 --> 00:28:40,099
Brother-in-law?

366
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:44,200
Su Jeong, I did this because you like it.

367
00:28:46,070 --> 00:28:47,549
Ok.

368
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:49,699
What is all this?

369
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:51,299
Okay.

370
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:53,479
Get a loan.

371
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:55,180
'Ah' the.

372
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:03,629
What?

373
00:29:03,630 --> 00:29:05,249
Why is it so beautiful?

374
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:06,929
Isn't it?

375
00:29:06,930 --> 00:29:08,399
A creation by Chef Ban Ju Yeon.

376
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:10,530
Let's eat.

377
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,729
How nice.

378
00:29:28,730 --> 00:29:33,350
Eating and talking together like this at home.

379
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:40,650
For the first time since my parents passed away.

380
00:29:41,690 --> 00:29:45,170
He must have been going through tough times.

381
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:51,629
Stay here.

382
00:29:51,630 --> 00:29:53,220
Sir?

383
00:29:54,380 --> 00:29:55,899
You worked very hard today.

384
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:57,979
Have a drink with us and stay here.

385
00:29:57,980 --> 00:29:59,769
We'll have breakfast together tomorrow as well.

386
00:29:59,770 --> 00:30:02,599
I'll prepare breakfast.

387
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:05,109
- Will that be a problem? - Of course.

388
00:30:05,110 --> 00:30:06,499
Let's share a room.

389
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:08,179
Your room is messy.

390
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:09,959
An important guest cannot sleep there.

391
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,979
Sleep with me in the master bedroom.

392
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:14,499
You snore like a storm.

393
00:30:14,500 --> 00:30:16,749
He can't sleep. You'll sleep in my room, won't you?

394
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:18,739
You both want me. This is a difficult situation.

395
00:30:18,740 --> 00:30:21,160
I only have one body.

396
00:30:21,750 --> 00:30:23,309
Only sleep in my room.

397
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:25,009
- Are you crazy? - Are you crazy?

398
00:30:25,010 --> 00:30:26,829
What are you thinking?

399
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:29,490
I can sleep in the living room.

400
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,650
Oh, okay.

401
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:18,529
Are you sleeping?

402
00:32:18,530 --> 00:32:21,670
If you're not asleep, could I see you briefly?

403
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:30,350
What's wrong?

404
00:32:40,430 --> 00:32:45,299
I bought this for you, but I realized I only bought one.

405
00:32:45,300 --> 00:32:48,099
If I had put it in the refrigerator, my father or Su Bin would have drunk it.

406
00:32:48,100 --> 00:32:50,049
I thought she was a good girl.

407
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:52,390
You're only interested in me.

408
00:32:53,190 --> 00:32:57,139
Thank you. I wanted something sweet.

409
00:32:57,140 --> 00:32:59,729
Are you okay after drinking alcohol?

410
00:32:59,730 --> 00:33:00,949
I am good.

411
00:33:00,950 --> 00:33:05,380
You're the only one who can kill me.

412
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,279
Anyway, what did you do today?

413
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,999
I told you to read comics and relax.

414
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:15,800
I ate tteokbokki with your brother and helped your father.

415
00:33:16,990 --> 00:33:18,439
Do you know?

416
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:21,410
I'm the kind of guy who knows how to change doorknobs.

417
00:33:22,230 --> 00:33:24,909
Unbelievable. Did you do that?

418
00:33:24,910 --> 00:33:28,149
You're a good cook too. You're good at everything.

419
00:33:28,150 --> 00:33:30,279
I know.

420
00:33:30,280 --> 00:33:32,710
I know how to do something.

421
00:33:34,020 --> 00:33:36,180
Good job.

422
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:40,299
Was everything alright with you?

423
00:33:40,300 --> 00:33:43,889
Yes, of course, everything was fine.

424
00:33:43,890 --> 00:33:45,889
That's good to hear.

425
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:47,499
Read comic books while you're here.

426
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:50,009
Really? Let's read it together.

427
00:33:50,010 --> 00:33:51,409
I'll suggest one to you.

428
00:33:51,410 --> 00:33:53,150
Sounds good.

429
00:33:56,250 --> 00:33:57,339
This is it.

430
00:33:57,340 --> 00:34:02,699
I read this when I'm feeling like a warrior.

431
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:05,079
- Did you get that signature? - Yes, that's right.

432
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:10,200
You could say this is one of my proudest achievements.

433
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:16,330
This is what happened...

434
00:34:17,450 --> 00:34:20,240
Look at the spot I've marked.

435
00:34:29,620 --> 00:34:32,499
You don't need to see me off.

436
00:34:32,500 --> 00:34:35,499
I wish I could take you to work.

437
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:38,770
But breakfast with family is more important.

438
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:41,699
Did you sleep well?

439
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:43,399
You should have slept comfortably at home.

440
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:45,849
My father and Su Bin went too far.

441
00:34:45,850 --> 00:34:47,149
I felt comfortable.

442
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:49,220
More than my home.

443
00:34:50,530 --> 00:34:52,859
That's a relief then.

444
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:56,739
I'm happy that you're a beloved sister and friend.

445
00:34:56,740 --> 00:34:59,229
That's why I can be loved.

446
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:01,240
Like family.

447
00:35:03,890 --> 00:35:05,109
Come in now.

448
00:35:05,110 --> 00:35:07,420
You'll be late for breakfast.

449
00:35:10,670 --> 00:35:12,310
I'm going.

450
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:16,790
Su Jeong.

451
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:24,760
I made my decision yesterday.

452
00:35:25,460 --> 00:35:29,760
I won't make you cry a third time.

453
00:35:38,390 --> 00:35:40,889
Then, return safely.

454
00:35:40,890 --> 00:35:43,939
Fall or injury.

455
00:35:43,940 --> 00:35:46,520
Don't worry about me either.

456
00:36:12,020 --> 00:36:14,050
[Personnel Assignment Notification]

457
00:36:23,300 --> 00:36:25,380
[Baek Su Jeong - Removal from Position or Transfer]

458
00:36:28,890 --> 00:36:30,839
What is this, Team Leader?

459
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:32,259
From where...

460
00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:34,139
This makes no sense.

461
00:36:34,140 --> 00:36:37,589
They can't do that based on a false rumor.

462
00:36:37,590 --> 00:36:41,219
The rumor is true.

463
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:42,329
Sir?

464
00:36:42,330 --> 00:36:44,109
You said then that wasn't the case.

465
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:46,169
With the director?

466
00:36:46,170 --> 00:36:49,229
I'm sorry. That wasn't right at the time.

467
00:36:49,230 --> 00:36:52,250
But we're leaving now.

468
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:55,319
Okay.

469
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:59,309
Okay, but still—yes, this is unfair.

470
00:36:59,310 --> 00:37:02,719
Team Leader, you're not going to brush this off like that.

471
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:04,530
Isn't it?

472
00:37:10,460 --> 00:37:14,740
I'm sorry this had to happen while I was busy.

473
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:24,090
Team Leader.

474
00:37:29,770 --> 00:37:33,429
Why did he send his girlfriend, who is rumored to be having an affair with his grandson, here?

475
00:37:33,430 --> 00:37:35,369
He probably has no skills whatsoever.

476
00:37:35,370 --> 00:37:36,909
That's why he sent him here.

477
00:37:36,910 --> 00:37:40,129
So he does nothing, gives up of his own accord, and leaves.

478
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:42,010
Excuse me.

479
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:45,719
I won't stand in your way.

480
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:49,989
If there's any task that's too much trouble for you, give it to me.

481
00:37:49,990 --> 00:37:53,070
I'm sure there are things I can do.

482
00:37:58,300 --> 00:38:01,139
W-What? What?

483
00:38:01,140 --> 00:38:05,059
Something must be wrong. It won't turn off.

484
00:38:05,060 --> 00:38:07,229
What? An hour?

485
00:38:07,230 --> 00:38:08,870
H-Hey...

486
00:38:09,570 --> 00:38:11,510
Let me give it a try.

487
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:14,679
This isn't something everyone can fix.

488
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:16,969
I have electrician and fire safety certifications.

489
00:38:16,970 --> 00:38:18,800
No problem, right?

490
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,710
It worked.

491
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:52,330
What else can I do?

492
00:38:57,180 --> 00:38:59,190
One minute.

493
00:39:02,460 --> 00:39:05,820
Why are you all standing here...?

494
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:19,829
What are you doing?

495
00:39:19,830 --> 00:39:22,339
I thought she wouldn't put up with things like that.

496
00:39:22,340 --> 00:39:24,789
And you? Why are you angry?

497
00:39:24,790 --> 00:39:28,709
I thought you'd be happy not to see annoying subordinates in meetings.

498
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:33,399
The reason I don't love you is because you can't tolerate anything.

499
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:35,718
I walked on eggshells and...

500
00:39:35,730 --> 00:39:38,399
...I gave up my self-respect to get this far.

501
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:40,409
But you can't tolerate anything.

502
00:39:40,410 --> 00:39:44,449
You say everything you want to say and you maintain your pride.

503
00:39:44,450 --> 00:39:46,409
You think you're superior.

504
00:39:46,410 --> 00:39:49,480
I really hated it, but...

505
00:39:50,950 --> 00:39:54,949
But seeing you put up with it—do you hate it now too?

506
00:39:54,950 --> 00:39:56,649
Yes.

507
00:39:56,650 --> 00:39:58,439
I hate it.

508
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:05,609
Baek Su Jeong, - why just... Senior, there are some things I haven't put up with until now...

509
00:40:05,610 --> 00:40:08,109
To protect myself.

510
00:40:08,110 --> 00:40:13,040
But to protect someone else, I have to put up with certain things.

511
00:40:14,170 --> 00:40:16,290
I'm leaving now.

512
00:40:51,010 --> 00:40:53,120
- Hello. - Hello.

513
00:40:58,340 --> 00:40:59,769
Please drink this.

514
00:40:59,770 --> 00:41:01,779
- Thank you. - Thank you.

515
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:03,809
Thanks.

516
00:41:03,810 --> 00:41:06,129
This is the new director.

517
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:09,770
Do you think that's all there is to it for Director Ban?

518
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:16,808
Ban Ju Yeon, the strategy team director at Yongsung Store, has been fired...

519
00:41:16,820 --> 00:41:21,819
...was removed and Park Ji Cheol from Yongsung Trading was hired for the position.

520
00:41:21,820 --> 00:41:25,489
This appointment, according to the source, was made by President Jeong Hyo...

521
00:41:25,501 --> 00:41:29,720
...it strongly reflects Seon's will.

522
00:41:34,740 --> 00:41:35,980
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

523
00:41:48,020 --> 00:41:50,070
[Preparations for Hana City Business Agreement Ceremony]

524
00:41:52,620 --> 00:41:53,979
[Will]

525
00:41:53,980 --> 00:41:55,360
[Throw it in the trash]

526
00:42:12,070 --> 00:42:13,599
Are you ok?

527
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,010
I heard the news.

528
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:18,600
Certainly.

529
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:21,380
Aren't you exaggerating?

530
00:42:22,090 --> 00:42:24,080
Does it seem that way?

531
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:31,150
But nobody would be okay in that situation.

532
00:42:31,940 --> 00:42:34,650
I should try to look happier.

533
00:42:35,450 --> 00:42:38,530
I have a request.

534
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:40,809
This...

535
00:42:40,810 --> 00:42:44,150
Can you keep this a secret from the director for now?

536
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:47,869
She'll be upset if she finds out.

537
00:42:47,870 --> 00:42:50,830
All he can do is tell me to quit my job.

538
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:53,729
According to me...

539
00:42:53,730 --> 00:42:56,229
That would be even better.

540
00:42:56,230 --> 00:42:59,140
You have the capacity to work anywhere.

541
00:42:59,870 --> 00:43:02,279
I know, but...

542
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:06,370
If I left, everything would be over completely.

543
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:11,020
That's why I'll try everything I can.

544
00:43:17,760 --> 00:43:19,820
[Grace]

545
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:23,839
That's when things should feel unsettling.

546
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:25,539
How is Su Jeong?

547
00:43:25,540 --> 00:43:27,939
She sounded cheerful on the phone.

548
00:43:27,940 --> 00:43:29,409
Okay, that's it.

549
00:43:29,410 --> 00:43:31,199
Personally, he was cheerful too.

550
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:33,119
I know it's not easy.

551
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:36,510
That's what happens when things get tough.

552
00:43:37,510 --> 00:43:39,780
- Welcome. - Welcome.

553
00:43:40,340 --> 00:43:43,460
- Mom. - Hey, Ha Jin. I-

554
00:43:44,140 --> 00:43:46,160
Who's this?

555
00:43:48,760 --> 00:43:51,429
Hi, I'm Ha Jin's male colleague—he's a part-time employee.

556
00:43:51,430 --> 00:43:54,019
Hey, why would you hire someone when you don't have any customers?

557
00:43:54,020 --> 00:43:55,699
That's why I just fired him.

558
00:43:55,700 --> 00:44:00,000
I will deposit the payment for the work you did.

559
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:03,529
I'm so, so sorry.

560
00:44:03,530 --> 00:44:04,859
I'll call you after my mother leaves.

561
00:44:04,860 --> 00:44:06,389
Can't I just be your boyfriend?

562
00:44:06,390 --> 00:44:08,249
Then he would have married us off right away.

563
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:10,180
That's fine with me.

564
00:44:13,140 --> 00:44:16,369
Ha Jin, it's been a long time.

565
00:44:16,370 --> 00:44:20,459
He asked me for help to convince you.

566
00:44:20,460 --> 00:44:22,610
Crazy jerk.

567
00:44:23,420 --> 00:44:26,009
Hey, what's your problem?

568
00:44:26,010 --> 00:44:28,339
They want to get back together.

569
00:44:28,340 --> 00:44:32,149
H-Ha Jin, Anne wants it very much too.

570
00:44:32,150 --> 00:44:34,129
Let's try to get things right.

571
00:44:34,130 --> 00:44:37,460
I miss the crab stew you used to make and...

572
00:44:38,530 --> 00:44:40,169
Being alone is very difficult.

573
00:44:40,170 --> 00:44:41,859
Hey!

574
00:44:41,860 --> 00:44:48,639
I quietly divorced you because I didn't want to regret the time I spent in my twenties with you.

575
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:52,449
So stop the nonsense and leave.

576
00:44:52,450 --> 00:44:54,809
Seo Ha Jin! Aman.

577
00:44:54,810 --> 00:44:56,359
Why are you so mean?

578
00:44:56,360 --> 00:45:00,399
When you got divorced, he also gave you money to open this shop.

579
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,939
Do you think you did this for me?

580
00:45:02,940 --> 00:45:04,570
What?

581
00:45:05,270 --> 00:45:06,599
So what then?

582
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:08,280
Ha Jin.

583
00:45:11,680 --> 00:45:12,570
What's wrong?

584
00:45:12,571 --> 00:45:15,399
If you have a conscience, you can't do this.

585
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:17,820
Especially in front of Anne.

586
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:22,709
I didn't get divorced for nothing.

587
00:45:22,710 --> 00:45:24,569
This jerk cheated on me.

588
00:45:24,570 --> 00:45:26,940
With another woman at work.

589
00:45:27,910 --> 00:45:30,410
What? Hey...

590
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:35,870
Is this true—M-Mom, um...

591
00:45:36,540 --> 00:45:38,659
It was a mistake.

592
00:45:38,660 --> 00:45:39,869
- A mistake. - A mistake?

593
00:45:39,870 --> 00:45:43,559
- M-Mom, I-I'm sorry. - Was it a mistake?

594
00:45:43,560 --> 00:45:44,779
- Mom! - Mom.

595
00:45:44,780 --> 00:45:47,020
- Mom. - Mom.

596
00:45:55,990 --> 00:45:59,640
Oh dear, I showed him all sorts of things.

597
00:46:06,780 --> 00:46:08,809
Seo Ha Jin.

598
00:46:08,810 --> 00:46:11,170
Mom, are you awake?

599
00:46:11,990 --> 00:46:13,649
Are you awake, darling?

600
00:46:13,650 --> 00:46:15,259
Safe.

601
00:46:15,260 --> 00:46:21,180
Hey, why didn't you tell me? Huh?

602
00:46:21,990 --> 00:46:24,119
I had no idea.

603
00:46:24,120 --> 00:46:27,950
Instead, I blamed my precious daughter.

604
00:46:31,060 --> 00:46:33,050
It must have hurt him.

605
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:35,849
It didn't hurt at all.

606
00:46:35,850 --> 00:46:39,009
Your fists are soft now.

607
00:46:39,010 --> 00:46:40,209
Oh no...

608
00:46:40,210 --> 00:46:42,909
Oh dear, poor me.

609
00:46:42,910 --> 00:46:45,900
Why should our daughter be treated like this...?

610
00:46:49,470 --> 00:46:52,650
I didn't tell you because I knew you'd be upset.

611
00:46:53,780 --> 00:46:56,019
Do you think I don't feel sorry when I blame you?

612
00:46:56,020 --> 00:46:57,299
Baby! Baby!

613
00:46:57,300 --> 00:47:00,119
Honey, calm down. Come on...

614
00:47:00,120 --> 00:47:03,269
It's good that we finally learned this.

615
00:47:03,270 --> 00:47:04,659
Safe...

616
00:47:04,660 --> 00:47:10,770
Even just putting it in the refrigerator and making cold sashimi wouldn't be enough.

617
00:47:13,750 --> 00:47:19,329
If he comes back again, call me first. Understood?

618
00:47:19,330 --> 00:47:22,300
- Okay. - Do you understand?

619
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:26,489
Yes, I'll call.

620
00:47:26,490 --> 00:47:28,039
Hey.

621
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:30,199
Meanwhile, the previous guy...

622
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:32,939
that part-time worker...

623
00:47:32,940 --> 00:47:35,020
Is he a boyfriend?

624
00:47:37,130 --> 00:47:39,480
Do you have a boyfriend?

625
00:47:42,310 --> 00:47:44,010
Yes.

626
00:47:44,910 --> 00:47:46,519
How old?

627
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:49,019
Is she divorced? Or just single?

628
00:47:49,020 --> 00:47:51,159
Does she want to get married?

629
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:52,379
Oh dear, Mom.

630
00:47:52,380 --> 00:47:53,909
Well...

631
00:47:53,910 --> 00:47:57,349
I realized he was very handsome.

632
00:47:57,350 --> 00:47:59,989
Oh, wait. I'm happy with how I am right now.

633
00:47:59,990 --> 00:48:02,480
You're fine now. Let's go.

634
00:48:08,990 --> 00:48:12,109
Mrs. Baek doesn't seem willing to leave quietly.

635
00:48:12,110 --> 00:48:17,170
Because people are noticing him here and there, there's more talk inside.

636
00:48:18,940 --> 00:48:21,210
What should I do?

637
00:48:31,500 --> 00:48:32,549
Yes.

638
00:48:32,550 --> 00:48:33,809
Did you call?

639
00:48:33,810 --> 00:48:35,240
Did I call?

640
00:48:35,960 --> 00:48:38,959
Oh, I must have pressed it while changing it.

641
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:41,000
Why did you change?

642
00:48:41,810 --> 00:48:44,759
Well, I spilled water on myself.

643
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:46,459
Have you had lunch?

644
00:48:46,460 --> 00:48:47,719
I haven't eaten it yet.

645
00:48:47,720 --> 00:48:49,319
Go and eat.

646
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:51,869
You know you need to eat well at times like these.

647
00:48:51,870 --> 00:48:53,499
There isn't much food at home.

648
00:48:53,500 --> 00:48:56,490
Shall we do some grocery shopping after work?

649
00:48:59,750 --> 00:49:03,439
Su Jeong, what's wrong?

650
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:07,210
I need to do something. I'll call you back.

651
00:49:26,390 --> 00:49:28,830
You wanted to see me, Madam President.

652
00:49:35,540 --> 00:49:38,019
From where...

653
00:49:38,020 --> 00:49:39,929
Are you fighting to stay?

654
00:49:39,930 --> 00:49:43,140
Can't you understand that I want you to leave quietly?

655
00:49:43,740 --> 00:49:47,750
Because the director might come back.

656
00:49:49,690 --> 00:49:51,559
I understand.

657
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:54,099
It was because you were stupid.

658
00:49:54,100 --> 00:49:59,339
I understand he wants to be the heir again, but this...

659
00:49:59,351 --> 00:50:04,319
I'm not interested in bringing back someone so incompetent.

660
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:06,849
Then that position will remain vacant forever.

661
00:50:06,850 --> 00:50:12,100
If the director isn't qualified, who can fill that position?

662
00:50:13,990 --> 00:50:15,999
How can you be so sure?

663
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:18,210
Because you...

664
00:50:18,830 --> 00:50:21,420
You are his only family.

665
00:50:22,100 --> 00:50:26,809
She worked hard to be recognized and loved by her only family.

666
00:50:26,810 --> 00:50:30,299
Do you think anyone else would work this hard?

667
00:50:30,300 --> 00:50:33,020
- What? - You don't know...

668
00:50:33,620 --> 00:50:36,259
How you feel too.

669
00:50:36,260 --> 00:50:42,270
Does it comfort you to blame your misfortunes on your grandchild?

670
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:48,959
And what I hope to get back is not the heir position.

671
00:50:48,960 --> 00:50:51,660
The director's family.

672
00:51:21,020 --> 00:51:23,139
Hey, Ju Yeon. Is everything alright?

673
00:51:23,140 --> 00:51:26,910
Brother, be honest with me.

674
00:51:29,260 --> 00:51:31,410
Too much...

675
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:37,619
Please have some of this.

676
00:51:37,620 --> 00:51:39,440
What's this?

677
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:46,349
What are you thinking?

678
00:51:46,350 --> 00:51:49,020
Doesn't it wake you up?

679
00:51:55,900 --> 00:51:57,639
After carrying these, we're done for today, right?

680
00:51:57,640 --> 00:51:59,059
Yes.

681
00:51:59,060 --> 00:52:02,319
It's nice to have a young person around.

682
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:04,660
It makes us so happy.

683
00:52:32,200 --> 00:52:33,909
What are you doing?

684
00:52:33,910 --> 00:52:35,829
You should have told me.

685
00:52:35,830 --> 00:52:38,679
Or you should have resigned immediately. Why...?

686
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:40,810
Are you doing this?

687
00:52:41,470 --> 00:52:43,299
Why are you putting up with this for me?

688
00:52:43,300 --> 00:52:44,809
Because I knew this would happen.

689
00:52:44,810 --> 00:52:48,329
Because you would blame yourself and feel bad.

690
00:52:48,330 --> 00:52:49,479
That's why I couldn't tell you.

691
00:52:49,480 --> 00:52:50,789
TRUE.

692
00:52:50,790 --> 00:52:54,499
You wouldn't have been a victim if it weren't for me.

693
00:52:54,500 --> 00:52:56,730
Why are you putting up with this?

694
00:52:57,460 --> 00:53:01,322
Because of a word from the mayor, I've spent this much time here...

695
00:53:01,334 --> 00:53:05,579
...should I just let the time and effort go to waste and leave?

696
00:53:05,580 --> 00:53:08,059
I made this decision for myself.

697
00:53:08,060 --> 00:53:10,830
Because I love you, and for myself.

698
00:53:11,640 --> 00:53:15,440
Because I had to stay here for what came next.

699
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:20,000
Therefore, please respect my decision.

700
00:53:23,110 --> 00:53:25,510
I'll make a decision then.

701
00:53:27,630 --> 00:53:29,700
For you, Su Jeong.

702
00:53:35,180 --> 00:53:36,639
Thank you.

703
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:38,789
You didn't have to drive me.

704
00:53:38,790 --> 00:53:39,989
Aren't you tired?

705
00:53:39,990 --> 00:53:41,689
Not at all.

706
00:53:41,690 --> 00:53:45,549
I must have exercised a lot to be able to do this.

707
00:53:45,550 --> 00:53:49,509
And it would be difficult to carry them alone.

708
00:53:49,510 --> 00:53:51,629
That's why I had to drive you today.

709
00:53:51,630 --> 00:53:53,569
What are all of these?

710
00:53:53,570 --> 00:53:55,029
For me?

711
00:53:55,030 --> 00:53:59,480
I'm sorry, but they're not for you.

712
00:54:00,300 --> 00:54:02,260
For your mother.

713
00:54:02,850 --> 00:54:07,029
And how about installing a security camera in the shop?

714
00:54:07,030 --> 00:54:10,499
Your ex-husband didn't look very well.

715
00:54:10,500 --> 00:54:13,200
You never know when he'll come back.

716
00:54:15,270 --> 00:54:17,330
Shin Won,

717
00:54:19,140 --> 00:54:27,289
I couldn't help then, but your worrying bothers me.

718
00:54:27,290 --> 00:54:31,470
Not to mention my ex-husband and my family.

719
00:54:32,550 --> 00:54:36,080
Regarding the gifts, I appreciate your thoughtfulness.

720
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:41,520
Drive home safely.

721
00:54:58,030 --> 00:54:59,770
Ha Jin.

722
00:55:02,230 --> 00:55:07,130
You just drew a line between us, didn't you?

723
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:11,450
Or...

724
00:55:12,150 --> 00:55:14,059
Only...

725
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:16,330
Can I ignore that line?

726
00:55:17,190 --> 00:55:18,820
Ben...

727
00:55:19,710 --> 00:55:22,249
I have so much fun when I'm with you.

728
00:55:22,250 --> 00:55:25,170
It excites me and makes me feel at home.

729
00:55:25,780 --> 00:55:29,460
That's why I want to share boring, painful, and sad things with you.

730
00:55:30,140 --> 00:55:32,460
I want it so much...

731
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:37,570
To become deeply involved in his life—but I'm saying I don't want that.

732
00:55:40,510 --> 00:55:42,960
Don't you understand what I'm saying?

733
00:55:43,870 --> 00:55:45,179
I understand.

734
00:55:45,180 --> 00:55:49,990
I know why you dislike it and why you're afraid, but—you don't understand.

735
00:55:51,460 --> 00:55:53,890
Then we can't do that.

736
00:56:17,650 --> 00:56:18,929
Where are you going?

737
00:56:18,930 --> 00:56:20,869
There is a signing ceremony today.

738
00:56:20,870 --> 00:56:22,869
The ceremony took place as part of the renovation project.

739
00:56:22,870 --> 00:56:25,629
Hana City is generously supporting this, isn't it?

740
00:56:25,630 --> 00:56:26,719
Yes.

741
00:56:26,720 --> 00:56:30,460
The Team Leader and Director had completed all the preparations.

742
00:56:32,910 --> 00:56:35,399
[Yongsung]

743
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:37,889
[Business Agreement for Global Tourism]

744
00:56:37,890 --> 00:56:38,989
Hello.

745
00:56:38,990 --> 00:56:41,560
Nice to see you.

746
00:56:42,570 --> 00:56:44,530
- Sit down. - Okay.

747
00:56:46,300 --> 00:56:50,160
Madam President, you need to step outside for a moment.

748
00:56:58,300 --> 00:57:01,895
Between Hana City and Yongsung Store...

749
00:57:01,907 --> 00:57:06,029
...we will launch a business agreement for global tourism.

750
00:57:06,030 --> 00:57:10,450
Please greet the Mayor of Hana City, Oh Hyeok Su.

751
00:57:18,030 --> 00:57:20,309
Next...

752
00:57:20,310 --> 00:57:22,420
I am really sad.

753
00:57:23,650 --> 00:57:26,550
What? What are they doing?

754
00:57:28,560 --> 00:57:30,540
One minute.

755
00:58:13,300 --> 00:58:16,780
My name is Ban Ju Yeon.

756
00:58:17,440 --> 00:58:18,609
Yes.

757
00:58:18,610 --> 00:58:23,830
This is Ban Ju Yeon, the Director of the Strategy Team at Yongsung Store.

758
00:58:46,730 --> 00:58:50,799
[My Dearest Enemy]

759
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:53,500
[Thank you to Shin Hyun Soo for his special participation]

760
00:59:17,730 --> 00:59:19,979
Your plan is to fire Team Leader Baek Su Jeong.

761
00:59:19,980 --> 00:59:21,249
Please withdraw.

762
00:59:21,250 --> 00:59:24,059
Team Leader! I missed you so much.

763
00:59:24,060 --> 00:59:25,899
But with one condition.

764
00:59:25,900 --> 00:59:28,809
The renovation project must be successful.

765
00:59:28,810 --> 00:59:31,049
Don't try to be responsible for everything.

766
00:59:31,050 --> 00:59:34,019
We agreed to lean on each other so as not to be alone.

767
00:59:34,020 --> 00:59:36,899
They are canceling the refresh performance.

768
00:59:36,900 --> 00:59:38,599
The opening is just around the corner.

769
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:41,929
If you fail, you will lose everything.

770
00:59:41,930 --> 00:59:43,519
Mine.

771
00:59:43,520 --> 00:59:45,380
Black Dragon.